<paragraph blockId="39.[159,1116,1376,1732]" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">
<emphasis box="[199,435,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Derivation of name.</emphasis>
Latin 
<emphasis box="[524,607,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">pileolus</emphasis>
diminutive of 
<emphasis box="[797,860,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">pileus</emphasis>
‘a cap’, referring to the form of the prodissoconch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[159,1116,1376,1732]" lastBlockId="40.[154,1111,1254,1444]" lastPageId="40" lastPageNumber="3214" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">
<emphasis box="[199,351,1440,1464]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Comparisons.</emphasis>
The only other carditid found on 
<collectingRegion box="[806,923,1439,1463]" country="Mauritius" name="Rodrigues" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Rodrigues</collectingRegion>
is referable to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bruguiere, 1792)" baseAuthorityName="Bruguiere" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[159,578,1471,1496]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[159,362,1472,1496]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Cardita variegata</emphasis>
(Bruguière, 1792)
</taxonomicName>
and in its juvenile stage has a less angular outline (
<figureCitation box="[257,381,1505,1529]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="39.[159,175,1208,1230]" captionTargetBox="[161,1111,175,1170]" captionTargetId="figure-131@39.[159,1116,170,1170]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGS. 124–129. (124–128) Centrocardita pileolata n. sp. (124, 125) Holotype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00039: (124) external left valve (MontageTM); (125) external right valve (SEM). (126–128) Paratype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00040 (SEM): (126) external; (127) prodissoconch; (128) hinge view. (129) Cardita variegata, NMW.Z. 2000.086.00033, external right valve." pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">figures 129</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[397,440,1505,1529]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="40.[154,170,1094,1116]" captionTargetBox="[157,1111,173,1054]" captionTargetId="figure-102@40.[154,1111,170,1056]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGS. 130–134. (130, 131) Centrocardita pileolata n. sp., holotype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00039 (SEM): (130) internal right valve showing brood area; (131) close-up of embryo. (132, 133) Cardita variegata, NMW.Z.2000.086.0003 (SEM): (132) internal right valve; (133) hinge view. (134) Centrocardita pileolata, holotype, hinge view (SEM)." pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">132</figureCitation>
), a simple prodissoconch and a hinge with poorly developed lateral teeth (
<figureCitation box="[388,503,1539,1563]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="40.[154,170,1094,1116]" captionTargetBox="[157,1111,173,1054]" captionTargetId="figure-102@40.[154,1111,170,1056]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGS. 130–134. (130, 131) Centrocardita pileolata n. sp., holotype, NMW.Z.2001.061.00039 (SEM): (130) internal right valve showing brood area; (131) close-up of embryo. (132, 133) Cardita variegata, NMW.Z.2000.086.0003 (SEM): (132) internal right valve; (133) hinge view. (134) Centrocardita pileolata, holotype, hinge view (SEM)." pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">figure 133</figureCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Viader" box="[528,688,1539,1563]" firstAuthor="Viader" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" pagination="127 - 155" refId="ref20923" refString="VIADER, R., 1951, New or unrecorded shells from Mauritius and its dependencies, Mauritius Institute Bulletin, 3 (2), 127 - 155." type="journal article" year="1951">Viader (1951)</bibRefCitation>
described two small carditids from 
<collectingCountry box="[159,275,1573,1597]" name="Mauritius" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Mauritius</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viader" authorityYear="1951" box="[291,485,1573,1597]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vaughani">
<emphasis box="[291,485,1573,1597]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Cardita vaughani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is equilateral with the maximum height axis running through the umbo, not behind the umbo as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. G. Oliver &amp; Holmes" authorityYear="2004" box="[750,886,1607,1631]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Centrocardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pileolata">
<emphasis box="[750,886,1607,1631]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">C. pileolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Viader" authorityYear="1951" box="[908,1084,1607,1631]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Cardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vinsoni">
<emphasis box="[908,1084,1607,1631]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Cardita vinsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is inequilateral but the ribs are nodulose rather than scaly, the prodissoconch is not capped, and the carmine and brown coloration is not present in the 
<collectingRegion country="Mauritius" name="Rodrigues" pageId="39" pageNumber="3213">Rodrigues</collectingRegion>
shells. Many small carditids have been described from southern Africa and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[267,373,1254,1278]" name="Australia" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Australia</collectingCountry>
and we have reviewed the relevant literature (
<bibRefCitation author="Bartsch" box="[942,1106,1254,1278]" firstAuthor="Bartsch" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" pagination="1 - 305" refId="ref19469" refString="BARTSCH, P., 1915, Report on the Turton collection of South African marine mollusks, with additional notes on other South African shells contained in the United States National Museum, Smithsonian Institution United States National Museum Bulletin, 91, 1 - 305." type="journal article" year="1915">Bartsch, 1915</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Turton" box="[154,312,1287,1311]" firstAuthor="Turton" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" refId="ref20839" refString="TURTON, W. H., 1932, The Marine Shells of Port Alfred, S. Africa (London: Oxford University Press)." type="book" year="1932">Turton, 1932</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard" box="[331,502,1287,1311]" firstAuthor="Barnard" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" pagination="361 - 593" refId="ref19430" refString="BARNARD, K. H., 1964, Contributions to the knowledge of South African marine mollusca. Part V Lamellibranchiata, Annals of the South African Museum, 47 (3), 361 - 593." type="journal article" year="1964">Barnard, 1964</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamprell and Healy" box="[521,842,1287,1311]" firstAuthor="Lamprell" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" refId="ref20058" refString="LAMPRELL, K. and HEALY, J., 1998, Bivalves of Australia, Vol. 2 (Leiden: Backhuys Publishers), 288 pp." type="book" year="1998">Lamprell and Healy, 1998</bibRefCitation>
). Most of the smaller taxa are referred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="E. A. Smith" authorityYear="1881" box="[425,536,1320,1344]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Carditella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[425,536,1320,1344]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Carditella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but some to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sacco" authorityYear="1899" box="[730,884,1320,1344]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Centrocardita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[730,884,1320,1344]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Centrocardita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s. g. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1925" box="[987,1101,1320,1344]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Vimentum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[987,1101,1320,1344]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Vimentum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and most are equilateral. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith, 1904)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[473,868,1353,1378]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Carditella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="laticosta">
<emphasis box="[473,693,1354,1378]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">Carditella laticosta</emphasis>
(Smith, 1904)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[889,1046,1353,1377]" name="South Africa" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">South Africa</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith, 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[154,613,1387,1411]" class="Bivalvia" family="Carditidae" genus="Carditella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carditida" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="exulata" subGenus="Vimentum">
<emphasis box="[154,435,1387,1411]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214">C. (Vimentum) exulata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smith" box="[459,605,1387,1411]" firstAuthor="Smith" pageId="40" pageNumber="3214" pagination="1 - 341" refId="ref20726" refString="SMITH, E. A., 1885, Report on the Lamellibronchiata. Reports of the Scientific Results of the voyage of HMS Challenger during the years of 1873 - 76, Zoology, 13, 1 - 341, 25 pls." type="book chapter" year="1885">Smith, 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(South Australia) have oblique outlines but have poorly ornamented ribs.
</paragraph>
